item.description: ! W O R K ~ I N ~ P R O G R E S S ! Quiz 1 Isomorphic Percentil (centile) Aphorism Lurid Apace Undemonstrative Florid Umber Juggernaut Slatternly Show Answers 1. 2. Often used in the reporting of scores from norm-referenced tests. For example, if a score is in the 86th percentile, it is higher than 86% of the other scores.
